<description>

When Edit mode is toggled on, a "Reset page to default" button appears at the top right and a "+ Add a block" button appears below the Dashboard heading. Clicking it opens an Add a block page listing all available block types: Comments, Course overview, Latest announcements, Latest badges, Learning plans, Logged in user, Mentees, Online users, Private files, Random glossary entry, Recently accessed courses, Starred courses, Tags, Text, and Upcoming events. A "Cancel" link at the bottom returns to the Dashboard without adding a block. In Edit mode, each existing block shows a move icon and a three-dot options menu for configure, move, and delete actions. Layout changes are persisted per user and can be fully reverted with "Reset page to default."

---


</description>

<workflows>
WF-001 | Reset page to default (while in Edit mode) | actor: <role> | branch: Edit_Mode == on | terminal: Reset page to default | on_success: reverts layout to default for the user
WF-002 | Open Add a block page (while in Edit mode) | actor: <role> | branch: Edit_Mode == on | terminal: + Add a block | on_success: opens Add_A_Block_Page
WF-003 | Cancel from Add a block page | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Cancel | on_success: returns to the Dashboard without adding a block
WF-004 | Move a block using the move icon (row-level) | actor: <role> | branch: Edit_Mode == on AND Blocks.Move_Icon | terminal: Move | on_success: initiates block repositioning; layout changes persisted for the user
WF-005 | Configure a block via options menu (row-level) | actor: <role> | branch: Edit_Mode == on AND Blocks.Options_Menu.Configure | terminal: Configure | on_success: opens configuration controls for the selected block
WF-006 | Move a block via options menu (row-level) | actor: <role> | branch: Edit_Mode == on AND Blocks.Options_Menu.Move | terminal: Move | on_success: initiates block repositioning; layout changes persisted for the user
WF-007 | Delete a block via options menu (row-level) | actor: <role> | branch: Edit_Mode == on AND Blocks.Options_Menu.Delete | terminal: Delete | on_success: removes the block from the dashboard; layout changes persisted for the user
</workflows>

